		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>five minute medding, using the same rules developed for health regen:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1. you must not be on any hate lists.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2. the effect ends if you cast a detrimental spell.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>3. your current mana regen with buffs, ft, aa, etc is doubled every minute, compounding.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>so, if your standing around with low buffs, etc, and your regen is only 40ish... minute 2 its now 80, minute 3 its now 160, minute 4 its now 320.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>your on a drogmor, full raid buffs... minute 1 its 108, minute 2 its now 216, minute 3 its now 432, etc.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>next, do the same for health, except times 3 or 4 if needed to make sure even those guys with 15k health get to full in 5 minutes or less.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>that reduces down times, including death, to minimal levels of wait.&nbsp; you can even do something similer for endurance.</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=411608">Hurk</a><br>~~~~~<br>"Character is always lost when a high ideal is sacrificed on the altar of conformity and popularity." - Anon<br><br>"You can tell the character of someone by how they treat those that can do nothing for them." -Hendrix
