		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<br><blockquote><hr>Hurk wrote:<br><DIV>five minute medding, using the same rules developed for health regen:</DIV><DIV> </DIV><DIV>1. you must not be on any hate lists.</DIV><DIV> </DIV><DIV>2. the effect ends if you cast a detrimental spell.</DIV><DIV> </DIV><DIV>3. your current mana regen with buffs, ft, aa, etc is doubled every minute, compounding.</DIV><DIV> </DIV><DIV>so, if your standing around with low buffs, etc, and your regen is only 40ish... minute 2 its now 80, minute 3 its now 160, minute 4 its now 320.</DIV><DIV> </DIV><DIV>your on a drogmor, full raid buffs... minute 1 its 108, minute 2 its now 216, minute 3 its now 432, etc.</DIV><DIV><br><hr></blockquote><br><br>Looks good on paper, but highly exploitable.<br><br>For example, wizard fighting vishimtar (or any other mob where the evac point is close to the fight point, which is almost everything in DoN--I picked vishimtar since it's a 30+ minute fight and the wizard could repeat this process several times).  Nukes to oom, casts self only evac.  Sits at safe point for 3-5 minutes and has a new full tank of mana.  Runs back in, repeat.<br><br>For necros it's even worse . . they don't have to evac they can just FD off aggro.<br><br><br>I would LOVE to see a percentage based regen.  I think the med idea is a good one.  Instead of providing a flat amount of regen, the meditate bonus be changed to a percentage.  SOE would have to determine "average" mana pools for each level (note that they've already sort of done this with /betabuff).  Then the med bonus could be changed from a flat amount to [(meditate skill)/12 * (your mana pool)/(avg.mana pool)] or something of that nature.<br><br>As someone hinted at above, making it percentage based basically means that it's something you will continue to use forever and ever, because it keeps getting better with you (such as defensive and divine arbitration).  But, I don't see that as a problem, because casters meditating is something that they are supposed to be doing forever and ever (at least I thought so), but as mana regen and mana pools get bigger and bigger, the med bonus is currently becoming less and less worthwhile.	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
