		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>With the 'expansive mind' AAs you can reach an FT cap of 20. With elixer of greater concentration (if you can afford them) this raises FT to 23.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I only have a 5300 mana pool, I am doing DoN Creator missions to get that up with Augments. I can keep a full group of level 65 to 70s (Im a 67) healed easily and can keep a 9.5 HP and 1700 AC tank up with Pious of Elixer and Panolpy of VIE and still be at 80% mana the whole mission. If the tank is geared better I use less mana. The 80% figure includes keeping the nuke happy wizard healed, the puller healed and the too quick to slow shaman or enchanter healed. And redoing conviction when it is debuffed.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>But I never sit down, I cast yaulp V throughout the entire mission and I always have a Clairvoyance on me from my Bot Enchanter. Casting Yaulp is tedious, but it keeps me at a minimum at 80% mana. If I find I am getting below 80m frequently then there is something seriously wrong with the groups abilities.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Currently I am at FT18. As the previous posters said a higher FT cap would be nice. I doubt at the raid level I could keep up with a 5300 mana pool.&nbsp; I do not use a mount and I find my YaulpV mana regen is better standing than the sitting regen. My examples given are all from DoNs.</DIV>	
