<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&message.id=9053#M9053">14</a> of 28
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 690 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Saroc_Luclin wrote:<BR><BR>I think what I'm trying to say here is the following:<BR>In a fairly constant group (ie one with few pauses between mobs), does Yaulping throughout give you a better total mana regen rate than the sitting method?<BR><BR>My gut feeling is that this does tend to be the case, but I'm not positive of it. I'm not even sure how to begin to work this sort of thing out concretely.<BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV>Actually Saroc you are correct.&nbsp; A guildmate of mine did the math a while back and YES, overall Yaulp 7 is better mana regen than sitting/mounted.&nbsp; You hit it right on the head that when using yaulp that 10-14 per tick remains constant where the 19 from sitting or mounted&nbsp;drops to 1&nbsp;when you are casting.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>To Demostarte: I will use myself as the example.&nbsp;lets say I am doing the sitting/mounted thing and each fight is 1 minute long and I am casting,1 mark of the blameless, 1 reproach, 2 cheals and 1 pious remedy per fight. MotB is a normal cast time of 3 (2.7 with Spell haste buff), reproach is a normal cast time of 6 (5.4 w/spell haste), 2 cheals are 20 secs and PR is 1.8 (spell haste does not effect anything below 2.0), so all told I am casting just about 30 seconds (20+2.7+5.4+1.8=29.9) of a 1 minute fight so that's 50/50 medding/casting.&nbsp; That means my average regen rate is 10/tick&nbsp;(19+1=20/2=10).</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Now lets assume worst case scenario: cleric with yaulp 5 and no mana preservation or buff extention.&nbsp; so Yaulp 5 costs 10 to cast and regens 10/tick over four ticks.&nbsp; So, the first tick counters the casting cost so over four ticks this cleric get 8.5/tick (40-10 = 30/4 = 8.5).</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Now lets assume a best case scenario: cleric wih yaulp 7, 30% mana pres, and 70% buff extention (that's me BTW). So yaulp costs 7 to cast and regens 14/tick.&nbsp; So the first HALF tick counters the casting cost over seven ticks I get 13/tick (14 x 7 = 98 -7 = 91/7 = 13)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>In BOTH yaulp cases amount of casting is meaningless to how much you regen since you regen the same amount all the time.&nbsp; Now the two examples above also assume "perfect" recast (new yaulp lands right when the old one fades.&nbsp; If you overlap by one tick the worst case you go down to 30-10 = 20/3 = 6.667 (significant), but the best case is 14x6 = 84 - 7 = 77/6 = 12.833 (marginal and still better).&nbsp; And I will bet that there are a few "worst case" clerics out there to those individuals sit and med between casts, to the rest use yaulp and (I just can't help myself :smileysurprised<img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0>) get in there and add melee and proc DPS, you'll be amazed at how much damage you do with a Delightful Orb of Forgotten Magic (LDoN - everfrost).</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>P.S.: dont let this degenerate into a battle cleric vs pure healer cleric flame vest.&nbsp; I put in that last comment because that's EXACTLY how I became the battle cleric I am today; I was using yaulp V in LDoN to avoid sit agro and decided to add what DPS I could since I was standing anyway.</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>08-09-2005</span> <span class=time_text>12:51 PM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
